// New:
case "plugins" -> p.getType().isPlugin();          // ToolType.PLUGIN
default        -> p.getCategory().getId().equalsIgnoreCase(currentCategory);
```
Note: `currentCategory` remains `String` because it receives sidebar navigation IDs ("all", "dev", "text", etc.). The `default` branch converts the plugin's enum `getId()` to a string for case-insensitive comparison.

#### 4b. DetailPanel.java

**File:** `/Users/phoebej/Develop/Java/SwissKitJ/SwissKit/src/main/java/fan/summer/ui/content/DetailPanel.java`

**Line 135**: `fillData()` method, `resolveColor()` call:
```java
// Current:
Color color = resolveColor(p.getIconStyle());

// New:
Color color = p.getIconStyle().getColor();
```

**Line 154**: `metaLabel.setText()`:
```java
// Current:
metaLabel.setText("v" + p.getVersion() + " · " + p.getType());

// New:
metaLabel.setText("v" + p.getVersion() + " · " + p.getType().getId());
```

**Line 158**: `typeVal.setText()`:
```java
// Current:
typeVal.setText(p.getType());

// New:
typeVal.setText(p.getType().getId());
```

**Line 159**: `categoryVal.setText()` uses `categoryName(p.getCategory())`. This is where we need a decision. Currently `categoryName()` is a private method (lines 174-182) that maps short codes to English display names. Options:
- Replace the switch with a map lookup using the enum's `getI18nKey()`, then resolve through `ResourceBundle`.
- Or, simpler for this migration: add a direct `displayName` to `ToolCategory` enum.

I recommend keeping it simpler: the `categoryName` method becomes a one-liner that looks up from a ResourceBundle, using `getI18nKey()` as the key. But since ResourceBundle is only available in the SwissKit module (not the API), this is done in the UI layer.

**Lines 162-172**: `resolveColor()` method -- **DELETE entirely**. Replaced by `IconStyle.getColor()`.

**Lines 174-182**: `categoryName()` method -- Replace the switch. Simplified version:
```java
private String categoryName(ToolCategory cat) {
    // Fall back to i18n key if no bundle is available
    return switch (cat) {
        case DEV   -> "Developer Tools";
        case TEXT  -> "Text Processing";
        case IMAGE -> "Image Processing";
        case NET   -> "Network Tools";
        default    -> "Other Tools";
    };
}
```
(Note: i18n integration can be done as a follow-up by looking up `cat.getI18nKey()` against a `ResourceBundle`.)

#### 4c. ToolCard.java

**File:** `/Users/phoebej/Develop/Java/SwissKitJ/SwissKit/src/main/java/fan/summer/ui/content/ToolCard.java`

**Line 33**: Icon color resolution:
```java
// Current:
Color iconColor = resolveColor(plugin.getIconStyle());

// New:
Color iconColor = plugin.getIconStyle().getColor();
```

**Line 49**: CSS class on icon wrapper:
```java
// Current:
iconWrap.getStyleClass().addAll("tool-icon-wrap", plugin.getIconStyle());

// New:
iconWrap.getStyleClass().addAll("tool-icon-wrap", plugin.getIconStyle().getCssClass());
```

**Line 65-66**: Type badge check and label:
```java
// Current:
boolean isPlugin = !"builtin".equals(plugin.getType());
Label tag = new Label(isPlugin ? "Plugin" : "Built-in");

// New:
boolean isPlugin = plugin.getType().isPlugin();
Label tag = new Label(isPlugin ? "Plugin" : "Built-in");
```

**Lines 120-130**: `resolveColor()` method -- **DELETE entirely**. Replaced by `IconStyle.getColor()`.

#### 4d. MainWindow.java

**File:** `/Users/phoebej/Develop/Java/SwissKitJ/SwissKit/src/main/java/fan/summer/ui/MainWindow.java`

**Line 64**: Plugin counting:
```java
// Current:
if(plugin.getType().equals("plugin") ) {
    pluginInTool++;
}else {
    buildInTool++;
}

// New:
if (plugin.getType().isPlugin()) {
    pluginInTool++;
} else {
    buildInTool++;
}
```

**Line 228**: Listener filter:
```java
// Current:
.filter(p -> !"builtin".equals(p.getType())).count();

// New:
.filter(p -> p.getType().isPlugin()).count();
```

#### 4e. Sidebar.java

**File:** `/Users/phoebej/Develop/Java/SwissKitJ/SwissKit/src/main/java/fan/summer/ui/sidebar/Sidebar.java`

**No changes needed.** The Sidebar uses its own `Category` record with `String id` (line 24), and all its ID values ("all", "text", "image", "dev", "net", "other", "plugins", "store", "fav", "settings") are pure UI navigation concepts. The fact that five of them ("dev", "text", "image", "net", "other") happen to share the same strings as `ToolCategory.getId()` values is a coincidence of the bridge in `ContentArea.matchesCategory()`. The Sidebar emits these strings to `ContentArea.showCategory(String)`, which passes them into `matchesCategory()`, which now does `p.getCategory().getId().equalsIgnoreCase(currentCategory)` -- this is the bridge point, not the Sidebar.

The `updateBadge(String categoryId, int count)` method at line 48 continues to work because it's keyed by the Sidebar's own navigation IDs.

---

### Step 5: Update OnlineStorePane (JSON String-to-Enum Conversion)

**File:** `/Users/phoebej/Develop/Java/SwissKitJ/SwissKit/src/main/java/fan/summer/ui/store/OnlineStorePane.java`

**Lines 183-184**: JSON parsing:
```java
// Current:
p.iconStyle = extractJsonString(obj, "iconStyle", "ic-blue");
p.category = extractJsonString(obj, "category", "other");

// New (convert to enums on parse):
String iconStyleStr = extractJsonString(obj, "iconStyle", "ic-blue");
p.iconStyle = IconStyle.fromCssClass(iconStyleStr);
String categoryStr = extractJsonString(obj, "category", "other");
p.category = ToolCategory.fromId(categoryStr);
```

**Lines 419-427**: `StorePlugin` inner class fields:
```java
// Current:
public static class StorePlugin {
    public String iconStyle;
    public String category;

// New:
public static class StorePlugin {
    public IconStyle iconStyle;
    public ToolCategory category;
```

**Line 263**: Category badge display:
```java
// Current:
Label categoryBadge = new Label(plugin.category);

// New:
Label categoryBadge = new Label(plugin.category.getId());
```

Note: `store.json` itself (in `docs/plugins/store.json`) keeps its string fields unchanged -- JSON cannot carry Java enums. The conversion happens in the Java parsing layer via `ToolCategory.fromId()` and `IconStyle.fromCssClass()`.

---

### Step 6: Migration Order (Sequenced)

The build depends on the API module being installed first. The migration must follow this order:

1. **Create the three enum files** in `SwissKitJ-Api/src/main/java/fan/summer/api/` (ToolCategory.java, IconStyle.java, ToolType.java). Build: `mvn install -f SwissKitJ-Api/pom.xml -DskipTests`.

2. **Update SwissKitJPlugin.java** in the API module. Rebuild and reinstall: `mvn install -f SwissKitJ-Api/pom.xml -DskipTests`.

3. **Update all 7 built-in tool implementations** in the SwissKit module. These depend on the updated interface, which is now available as a Maven dependency after step 2.

4. **Update UI consumers** in this order (all in SwissKit module):
   - `ToolCard.java` (removes `resolveColor()` duplicate, uses `getColor()` and `getCssClass()`)
   - `DetailPanel.java` (removes `resolveColor()` duplicate, uses `getColor()`, updates `categoryName()`)
   - `ContentArea.java` (replaces `"builtin".equals()` check, updates category matching)
   - `MainWindow.java` (replaces getType string comparisons with `isPlugin()`/`isBuiltin()`)
   - `OnlineStorePane.java` (adds string-to-enum conversion for JSON parsing)

5. **Full build verification**: `mvn clean package -DskipTests` from the repo root.

---

### Step 7: Consideration of Risks and Edge Cases

**Backward compatibility**: External plugins implementing `SwissKitJPlugin` that override `getType()` or `getIconStyle()` will fail to compile because the return type changed from `String` to the enum. Since the project is pre-release v3.0.0 on an active development branch, this is an acceptable breaking change. Plugin developers update their code from:
```java
@Override public String getCategory() { return "dev"; }
```
to:
```java
@Override public ToolCategory getCategory() { return ToolCategory.DEV; }
```

**plate icon wrap class**: `ToolCard` line 49 currently calls `iconWrap.getStyleClass().addAll("tool-icon-wrap", plugin.getIconStyle())`. After migration this becomes `.addAll("tool-icon-wrap", plugin.getIconStyle().getCssClass())`. The CSS file `glass.css` lines 224-230 have empty placeholder classes (`.ic-blue { }` etc.) that will continue to work since the CSS class strings are unchanged.

**Case-insensitive matching**: The current `ContentArea.matchesCategory()` uses `equalsIgnoreCase()` at line 272. The new `ToolCategory.fromId()` also uses `equalsIgnoreCase()`, preserving the same flexibility for sidebar-to-plugin matching.

**store.json format**: Unchanged. The `"iconStyle"` and `"category"` fields stay as JSON strings. Conversion to enums happens in `OnlineStorePane.parsePluginJson()` via the factory methods.

**i18n**: The `ToolCategory` enum carries `getI18nKey()` ("developer.tools", "text.processing", etc.) for future i18n integration. The current `DetailPanel.categoryName()` switch remains as a simple English fallback. The i18n resource bundles would need new keys added as a follow-up task.

---

### Critical Files for Implementation

- `/Users/phoebej/Develop/Java/SwissKitJ/SwissKitJ-Api/src/main/java/fan/summer/api/SwissKitJPlugin.java`
- `/Users/phoebej/Develop/Java/SwissKitJ/SwissKit/src/main/java/fan/summer/ui/content/DetailPanel.java`
- `/Users/phoebej/Develop/Java/SwissKitJ/SwissKit/src/main/java/fan/summer/ui/content/ToolCard.java`
- `/Users/phoebej/Develop/Java/SwissKitJ/SwissKit/src/main/java/fan/summer/ui/content/ContentArea.java`
- `/Users/phoebej/Develop/Java/SwissKitJ/SwissKit/src/main/java/fan/summer/ui/store/OnlineStorePane.java`

